🚀 FastAPI Cheat Sheet (Practical + Examples)
🧱 1. Basic Setup
from fastapi import FastAPI

app = FastAPI()

@app.get("/")
def home():
    return {"message": "Hello World"}

Run:

uvicorn app:app --reload
🌐 2. HTTP Methods
GET
@app.get("/users")
def get_users():
    return ["user1", "user2"]
POST
@app.post("/users")
def create_user():
    return {"message": "User created"}
PUT
@app.put("/users/{id}")
def update_user(id: int):
    return {"id": id, "status": "updated"}
DELETE
@app.delete("/users/{id}")
def delete_user(id: int):
    return {"id": id, "status": "deleted"}
🔢 3. Path Parameters
@app.get("/items/{item_id}")
def get_item(item_id: int):
    return {"item_id": item_id}

👉 Auto validation: /items/abc → error

❓ 4. Query Parameters
@app.get("/search")
def search(q: str, limit: int = 10):
    return {"query": q, "limit": limit}

Example:

/search?q=phone&limit=5
📦 5. Request Body (IMPORTANT)
Without Model
@app.post("/chat")
def chat(request: dict):
    return {"message": request["message"]}
With Pydantic Model (BEST PRACTICE)
from pydantic import BaseModel

class ChatRequest(BaseModel):
    message: str
    user_id: int

@app.post("/chat")
def chat(req: ChatRequest):
    return {"message": req.message}
📤 6. Response Model
class ChatResponse(BaseModel):
    reply: str
    intent: str

@app.post("/chat", response_model=ChatResponse)
def chat(req: ChatRequest):
    return {
        "reply": "Hello",
        "intent": "greeting"
    }
⏱️ 7. Async vs Sync
Sync
@app.get("/sync")
def sync_func():
    return {"msg": "sync"}
Async (better for APIs)
@app.get("/async")
async def async_func():
    return {"msg": "async"}

👉 Use async when calling APIs / DB

🧠 8. Dependency Injection (VERY USEFUL)
def common():
    return {"token": "abc123"}

@app.get("/secure")
def secure(dep=Depends(common)):
    return dep
🔐 9. Headers
from fastapi import Header

@app.get("/headers")
def read_headers(user_agent: str = Header()):
    return {"User-Agent": user_agent}
🍪 10. Cookies
from fastapi import Cookie

@app.get("/cookies")
def read_cookie(session_id: str = Cookie(None)):
    return {"session": session_id}
📁 11. File Upload
from fastapi import File, UploadFile

@app.post("/upload")
def upload(file: UploadFile = File(...)):
    return {"filename": file.filename}
📡 12. Calling External APIs
import requests

@app.get("/external")
def call_api():
    res = requests.get("https://api.github.com")
    return res.json()
🧠 13. Background Tasks
from fastapi import BackgroundTasks

def log_task(msg: str):
    print(msg)

@app.post("/task")
def run_task(background_tasks: BackgroundTasks):
    background_tasks.add_task(log_task, "Hello")
    return {"status": "running"}
⚠️ 14. Error Handling
from fastapi import HTTPException

@app.get("/error")
def error():
    raise HTTPException(status_code=404, detail="Not found")
📊 15. Middleware
@app.middleware("http")
async def log_requests(request, call_next):
    print("Request received")
    response = await call_next(request)
    return response
🧾 16. Logging Example (USE THIS)
import time

@app.post("/process")
def process(req: dict):
    start = time.time()

    response = "ok"

    print({
        "query": req.get("message"),
        "time": time.time() - start
    })

    return {"reply": response}
🧩 17. Modular Structure (IMPORTANT FOR YOUR PROJECT)

Instead of one file:

ai-service/
 ├── app.py
 ├── routes/
 │    └── chat.py
 ├── models/
 ├── services/
Example:
routes/chat.py
from fastapi import APIRouter

router = APIRouter()

@router.post("/process")
def process():
    return {"msg": "ok"}
app.py
from fastapi import FastAPI
from routes.chat import router

app = FastAPI()
app.include_router(router)
